parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulator can cause the window to fall into the door, making it difficult or impossible to close, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The window falls into the door
the window does not roll up or down

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sunroof can cause the glass to shatter or explode, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the spark plug can cause the engine to malfunction, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Loud popping sounds from under the engine

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Rear axle/differential failure can cause the vehicle to vibrate, lose power, or become difficult to control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Shift cable failure can cause the vehicle to roll backward or forward unexpectedly, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle rolls backward or forward unexpectedly
vehicle cannot be put in park.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Cruise control failure can cause the vehicle to lose speed control, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Cruise control shuts off without warning
cruise control does not work properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Spark plug failure can cause the engine to misfire, leading to decreased performance, poor fuel efficiency, and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: Spark plugs may blow out of the engine
or become stuck in the engine block. This can result in engine hesitation

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine may produce unusual noises
such as knocking or clunking sounds
or exhibit signs of overheating. In severe cases
the engine may seize or fail

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cam phaser failure can cause the engine to run rough, leading to decreased performance, poor fuel efficiency, and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
symptoms: The engine may produce unusual noises
such as tapping or clunking sounds

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause the vehicle to hesitate or fail to shift gears, potentially leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission may produce unusual noises

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold failure can cause the engine to run rough, leading to decreased performance, poor fuel efficiency, and potentially causing damage to other engine components.
